<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id0dd8192d-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795" identifier="/us/usc/t20/s3422"><num value="3422">§ 3422.</num><heading> Office of Inspector General</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There shall be in the Department an Office of Inspector General, established in accordance with chapter 4 of title 5.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id0dd8192e-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795">(<ref href="/us/pl/96/88/tII/s211">Pub. L. 96–88, title II, § 211</ref>, formerly § 212, <date date="1979-10-17">Oct. 17, 1979</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/93/675">93 Stat. 675</ref>; renumbered § 211, <ref href="/us/pl/103/382/tII/s271/a/2">Pub. L. 103–382, title II, § 271(a)(2)</ref>, <date date="1994-10-20">Oct. 20, 1994</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/108/3929">108 Stat. 3929</ref>; amended <ref href="/us/pl/117/286/s4/b/41">Pub. L. 117–286, § 4(b)(41)</ref>, <date date="2022-12-27">Dec. 27, 2022</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/136/4348">136 Stat. 4348</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id0dd8192f-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id0dd81930-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="priorProvisions" id="id0dd81931-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Prior Provisions</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">A prior <ref href="/us/pl/96/88/s211">section 211 of Pub. L. 96–88</ref> was renumbered section 210 and is classified to <ref href="/us/usc/t20/s3421">section 3421 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id0dd81932-3a70-11f1-a648-bee82ed8a795"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2022—<ref href="/us/pl/117/286">Pub. L. 117–286</ref> substituted “chapter 4 of title 5.” for “the Inspector General Act of 1978.”</p>
</note>
</notes>
